# React 19 — Event Types

This project uses **React 19**. Prefer current event types; deprecated ones trigger TS/IDE warnings.

## Form submit

Use **`SubmitEvent`** (or `SubmitEventHandler`) for `<form onSubmit>` — not `FormEvent`.

```tsx
// ✅ Good
const handleSubmit = async (e: React.SubmitEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {
  e.preventDefault();
};

// ❌ Bad — FormEvent is deprecated for submit handlers in React 19
const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {
  e.preventDefault();
};
```

## Input / select change

Use **`ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement | HTMLSelectElement | HTMLTextAreaElement>`** for `onChange`.

## Required string fields

Do not map empty required strings to `undefined` before validation — use `""` and validate with `(value ?? "").trim()` to avoid runtime errors on `.trim()`.

```tsx
// ✅ Good
if (!(form.name ?? "").trim()) {
  errors.name = "Name is required.";
}

// ❌ Bad — throws if name was stored as undefined
if (!form.name.trim()) {
  errors.name = "Name is required.";
}
```
